RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOULSTONE tracked leader to the half, drew clear to the far turn, stayed on gamely in the final furlong to stay clear under good handling. BACK UP GHOST no hurry from third spot to the turn, rallied on the wrong lead from the quarter pole to eighth pole to pull even with the winner but could not match strides with the winner and settled for the place spot while clearly best of the rest. JOEZINE never menaced while far back for show spot in the stretch run. SAINT SISTA was anxious behind gate and reluctant to load, showed good speed to half but folded from that point.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELTERRA PARK RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 17800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR OHIO BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Ove r Since April 18, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Claiming Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Ohio Registered Foals Preferred)(Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $15,000). (If transferred to the Main Track, this race will be run at One Mile and 70 Yards.) (Rail at 14 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JURA speed to the front under comfortable handling, stayed clear throughout and stayed game late with an impressive effort. BRILLIANT JOURNEY sharp break, chased winner throughout with no bid to get past. AMENDED steady run from outside to far turn, ran to finish up well in the stretch run with a good effort. FUTURE VICTORY raced back early on, ran on to contention at the half leveled off. HEMP HEMP HURRAY inside run saved ground to far turn angled out while mildly late. HONKY TONK HERO inside run to far turn, angled out stretch with good energy late. ALL ABOUT CROGE verty rank from the gate, settled down to secure the rail to the far turn, split horses in the stretch stretch and finished up with good energy. SAN MARCO CITY had trouble from the gate then never factored while under pressure and urged on with no response from the far turn to the finish. GOLDEN TEXT tracked to pair to the half with nothing left and dropped back steadily from the quarter pole. The 8th race was hand timed due to a malfunction with the timing system at Belterra Park on Thursday May 18th.
